{
  "stem": "8527.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not at that age, not till basically when the war started.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "About 1939, that's when I became more aware of it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was more aware of other feelings, I was-- of religious conflicts that I had as a child.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that started very young with me, and I'm-- I'm very surprised at that.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I was supposedly very skinny.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And my mother used to want to fatten me up, so she would slip-- take me in the back yard and slip some non-kosher meats.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But then I would have nightmares that I would be going to hell, that I would be-- because I ate treyf.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And in cheder you learn that if you committed any type of sins that there was a ladder to go up to heaven.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And any time you committed a sin, one of the rungs would be gone, and you'd never make it up to heaven.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I think I must have been five, six years old, and I was already preoccupied with death and-- and heaven and hell.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "My God was a very vengeful, vengeful God.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "That's my recollection.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My dad was.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My mother wasn't.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She came from a family of-- of 12 children, and more boisterous type and rowdy.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My dad was sort of on the quiet side, sedate.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He came, I think, from a more religious family.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "In fact, his father-- I was named after his dad, and my sister was named after his mother.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "My grandfather's name was Nachman Aaron, and naturally I never knew him.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So there was somewhat of a conflict, I think, in their ideology.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And from what I understand as a kid, I think it was also a fixed marriage because she was more the aggressive type and the outgoing, and he was the opposite.",
      "word_count": 31
    }
  ],
